AgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. The deployment/spec.md document defines the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation. The Helm chart enables reproducible deployments, configuration management via values.yaml, namespace-scoped installations, optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler), and CRD lifecycle management.\\n20: \\n21: ---\\n22: \\n23: ## Requirements\\n24: \\n25: ### AR-030-001: Chart 结构与元数据\\n26: \\n27: The Helm chart SHALL provide proper structure and metadata for Helm 3 compatibility.\\n28: \\n29: #### Scenario: AR-030-001-A — Chart.yaml 包含正确的元数据\\n30: \\n31: - **GIVEN** a chart directory at `manifests/charts/base/`\\n3...\n  Line 20: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775871558592,\"sessionID\":\"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7a30b52b0019tTgX0um87ls23\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7a30a9ae0010jlW9biSrcsUzO\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_f9d3d68f8cc64d77aa43dbfd\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# AR-030 — Helm Chart Templates and Values\\n\\n- **AR ID**: AR-030\\n- **Module**: manifests\\n- **Language**: YAML\\n- **Size**: L\\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\\n- **Stage**: ST-1\\n\\n## 1. Architecture\\n\\n### 1.1 Overview\\n\\nThe AgentCube Helm chart provides a declarative, reusable deployment mechanism for Kubernetes clusters. The chart packages Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, RBAC resources, and CRDs into a single installable unit with configurable values.\\n\\n### 1.2 Chart Structure\\n\\n```\\nmanifests/charts/base/\\n├── Chart.yaml\\n├── values.yaml\\n├── crds/\\n│   ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\\n│   └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\\n└── templates/\\n    ├── _helpers.tpl\\n    ├── workloadmanager.yaml\\n    ├── agentcube-router.yaml\\n    ├── rbac/\\n    │   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\\n    │   └── router.yaml\\n    └── volcano/\\n        └── agent-scheduler.yaml\\n```\\n\\n### 1.3 Components\\n\\n| Component | Kind | Required | Description |\\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\\n| Workload Manager | Deployment + Service | Yes | Agent session management |\\n| Router | Deployment + Service | Yes | API routing layer |\\n| WorkloadManager RBAC | ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding | Yes | Cluster-wide permissions |\\n| Router RBAC | ServiceAccount + Role + RoleBinding | Optional | Namespace-scoped permissions |\\n| Volcano Scheduler | Multiple (SA, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) | Optional | Custom scheduler |\\n| CRDs | CustomResourceDefinition | Yes | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\\n\\n## 2. Data Structures\\n\\n### 2....\n  Line 23: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775871563019,\"sessionID\":\"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7a318bb4001JYS3R7mt3F5vzz\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7a3183f9001LckdV6aAGREXEg\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Created `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md` with the technical implementation details for AR-030 (Helm Chart templates and values).\\n\\nThe document includes:\\n- **Architecture**: Chart structure, components, directory layout\\n- **Data Structures**: Chart.yaml, values.yaml schema with all configuration options\\n- **API Contracts**: Detailed specs for Workload Manager, Router, RBAC, and Volcano scheduler\\n- **Error Handling**: Validation and runtime error scenarios\\n- **Testing Strategy**: Unit tests, integration tests, and test commands\\n- **Acceptance Criteria**: 13 criteria for validation\\n- **Dependencies and Non-Requirements**: As specified in delta-spec.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775871563018,\"end\":1775871563018}}}\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/openc