pe>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\\n2: \\n3: ## Summary\\n4: \\n5: Implement the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\\n6: \\n7: ## Purpose\\n8: \\n9: ### Background\\n10: \\n11: AgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. Currently, the system lacks a formal Helm chart for production deployments. The deployment/design.md and deployment/spec.md documents define the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation.\\n12: \\n13: The Helm chart enables:\\n14: - Reproducible deployments across environments\\n15: - Configuration management via values.yaml\\n16: - Namespace-scoped installations\\n17: - Optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler)\\n18: - CRD lifecycle management\\n19: \\n20: ### Goal\\n21: \\n22: Create a complete Helm 3 chart at `manifests/charts/base/` that:\\n23: - Renders Workload Manager Deployment + Service\\n24: - Renders Router Deployment + Service\\n25: - Renders RBAC resources (ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, optional Role)\\n26: - Optionally renders Volcano agent scheduler resources\\n27: - Ships CRDs for AgentCube runtime custom resources\\n28: - Provides comprehensive v...\n  Line 27: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775871462372,\"sessionID\":\"ses_285d27a16ffe0wLYGNrj8mZFua\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7a2ef7e90015d127e2465R1CE\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7a2ee016001APUl0alYmcTRdI\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_285d27a16ffe0wLYGNrj8mZFua\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_98d71152a7d942dd99a933dc\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\\n\\n## Base Specifications\\n\\n- **AR**: AR-030\\n- **Module**: `manifests`\\n- **Language**: YAML\\n- **Size**: L\\n- **Base Specs**: `deployment/spec.md`, `deployment/design.md`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Background\\n\\nAgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. The deployment/spec.md document defines the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation. The Helm chart enables reproducible deployments, configuration management via values.yaml, namespace-scoped installations, optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler), and CRD lifecycle management.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Requirements\\n\\n### AR-030-001: Chart 结构与元数据\\n\\nThe Helm chart SHALL provide proper structure and metadata for Helm 3 compatibility.\\n\\n#### Scenario: AR-030-001-A — Chart.yaml 包含正确的元数据\\n\\n- **GIVEN** a chart directory at `manifests/charts/base/`\\n- **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\\n- **THEN** it SHALL pass without errors\\n- **AND** the chart SHALL have `name: agentcube` and `version: 0.1.0` in Chart.yaml\\n\\n#### Scenario: AR-030-001-B — values.yaml 包含所有必需配置项\\n\\n- **GIVEN** the `values.yaml` file exists in the chart\\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain keys for `redis.addr`, `redis.password`, `workloadmanager.*`, `router.*`, and ...\n  Line 30: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775871471051,\"sessionID\":\"ses_285d27a16ffe0wLYGNrj8mZFua\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7a302061001rQASELzdU46fwU\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7a300c120010ja8fXeLSiJJn6\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_285d27a16ffe0wLYGNrj8mZFua\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Done. I've written the delta-spec.md for AR-030 with 10 requirement sections and 33 GIVEN/WHEN/THEN acceptance scenarios covering:\\n\\n- **AR-030-001**: Chart structure and metadata\\n- **AR-030-002**: Helm installat