_1d420b43599948cf8d391c7e\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nImplement the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n### Background\\n\\nAgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. Currently, the system lacks a formal Helm chart for production deployments. The deployment/design.md and deployment/spec.md documents define the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation.\\n\\nThe Helm chart enables:\\n- Reproducible deployments across environments\\n- Configuration management via values.yaml\\n- Namespace-scoped installations\\n- Optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler)\\n- CRD lifecycle management\\n\\n### Goal\\n\\nCreate a complete Helm 3 chart at `manifests/charts/base/` that:\\n- Renders Workload Manager Deployment + Service\\n- Renders Router Deployment + Service\\n- Renders RBAC resources (ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, optional Role)\\n- Optionally renders Volcano agent scheduler resources\\n- Ships CRDs for AgentCube runtime custom resources\\n- Provides comprehensive values.yaml for configuration\\n\\n### Value\\n\\n- **Standardization**: Follows Kubernetes community conventions\\n- **Operational Efficiency**: Single command deployment with configurable parameters\\n- **Flexibility**: Optional components and extensive customization via values\\n- **Security**: Proper RBAC with minimal privileges\\n- **Maintainability**: Template-driven, version-controlled deployments\\n\\n---\\n\\n##...\n  Line 34: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775871294871,\"sessionID\":\"ses_285d5f3a3ffeBQhx48Y79H3M06\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7a2d76f0001j9B07cYCRjOj56\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7a2d6387001g4GWIwzxjAuJuO\",\"sess